---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import RelatedServices from '../../../components/RelatedServices.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Real Estate Translation in Dubai | OnlineTranslation.ae"
  description="Real estate document translation in Dubai. Title deeds, SPAs, contracts, and developer documents for property transactions. MOJ certified."
>
  <section class="hero-section bg-dark" data-theme="dark">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">HOME</a>
        <span class="separator">&gt;</span>
        <a href="/industries/">INDUSTRIES</a>
        <span class="separator">&gt;</span>
        <span class="current">REAL ESTATE</span>
      </nav>
      
      <h1>Real Estate Translation</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Property Documentation Experts</p>
      <p class="hero-intro">Dubai's property market involves buyers, sellers, and investors from around the world. We translate the documents that make property transactions possible, from initial SPAs to title deed transfers.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Understanding Dubai's Real Estate Document Landscape</h2>
      <div class="content-prose">
        <p>Property transactions in Dubai involve multiple authorities and document types. Dubai Land Department (DLD) handles registration and ownership records. Developers issue sales agreements and handover documentation. Banks require translated documents for mortgage processing. Each party has specific requirements, and missing or incorrect documentation causes delays.</p>
        
        <p>International buyers—who comprise a significant portion of Dubai's property market—face additional complexity. Documents from their home countries may need <a href="/services/attestation/">attestation</a> and translation before UAE authorities will accept them. Powers of Attorney enabling remote transactions must be properly certified. Marriage certificates and company documents may be required depending on ownership structure.</p>
        
        <h3>The Role of MOJ-Certified Translation</h3>
        <p>Dubai Land Department requires Arabic documentation for property registration. Foreign-language SPAs, title deeds, and supporting documents must be translated by MOJ-licensed translators. The certification provides official status that DLD accepts without question.</p>
        
        <p>For mortgage applications, banks similarly require certified translations of any foreign-language documents. This includes personal documents (passport translation is sometimes needed), income documentation, and corporate documents for company-owned properties.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Property Documents We Handle</h2>
      
      <div class="service-grid">
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon"><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i></div>
          <h3>Sale and Purchase Agreements</h3>
          <p>Off-plan and secondary market SPAs, reservation forms, and purchase agreements. All developer contract formats.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon"><i class="fas fa-landmark"></i></div>
          <h3>Title Deeds</h3>
          <p>Translation for DLD registration, mortgage applications, property transfers, and inheritance proceedings.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon"><i class="fas fa-handshake"></i></div>
          <h3>Lease Agreements</h3>
          <p>Residential and commercial leases for Ejari registration, legal disputes, and corporate records.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon"><i class="fas fa-building"></i></div>
          <h3>Developer Documents</h3>
          <p>Oqood registrations, handover documents, snagging reports, and developer correspondence.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Supporting Property Transactions</h2>
      <div class="content-prose">
        <h3>Off-Plan Purchases</h3>
        <p>Off-plan buyers sign SPAs with developers, often in English. Oqood (interim) registration with DLD may require Arabic translation. We translate SPAs, payment plans, and all developer correspondence to ensure buyers understand their commitments and have documentation ready for registration.</p>
        
        <h3>Secondary Market Sales</h3>
        <p>Resale transactions involve SPAs between buyer and seller, often facilitated by agents. Both parties may need translated documents—buyers proving source of funds, sellers demonstrating ownership history. We work with agents and conveyancers to provide timely translation that keeps transactions moving.</p>
        
        <h3>Mortgage and Financing</h3>
        <p>Banks require extensive documentation for property financing. Income proof, employment letters, company documents for self-employed buyers—all may need translation. Some banks have specific formatting requirements; we understand what major UAE banks expect.</p>
        
        <h3>Remote and International Buyers</h3>
        <p>Many Dubai property purchases happen remotely. Buyers in London, Mumbai, or Moscow sign documents and grant <a href="/legal/corporate/poa/">Powers of Attorney</a> to complete transactions in their absence. These POAs must be properly translated and may require attestation. We coordinate translation and attestation for remote buyers, often working directly with their representatives in Dubai.</p>
        
        <p><a href="/locations/dubai/palm-jumeirah/">Palm Jumeirah</a> in particular attracts international investors who may never visit during the purchase process. We provide comprehensive documentation support for these remote transactions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>For Real Estate Professionals</h2>
      
      <div class="benefits-grid">
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
          <div>
            <h4>Fast Turnaround</h4>
            <p>Same-day service for urgent transactions. We understand deal timelines and registration deadlines.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
          <div>
            <h4>DLD Compliance</h4>
            <p>Documents formatted to Dubai Land Department requirements. No rejections for formatting issues.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
          <div>
            <h4>Volume Arrangements</h4>
            <p>Preferential rates for agents and developers with regular translation needs. Dedicated account support.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="benefit-item">
          <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
          <div>
            <h4>Developer Partnerships</h4>
            <p>We work with several major developers on ongoing translation needs for international sales.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Working With Agents and Conveyancers</h2>
      <div class="content-prose">
        <p>Real estate agents facilitate most Dubai property transactions. We support agents by providing reliable, fast translation that keeps deals on track. When a buyer needs documents translated urgently for a registration appointment, we accommodate the timeline.</p>
        
        <h3>Agent Benefits</h3>
        <p>Agents who refer clients to us receive responsive service that reflects well on their professionalism. We provide accurate quotes quickly, deliver on promised timelines, and communicate clearly throughout the process. Your clients become our priority.</p>
        
        <h3>Conveyancing Support</h3>
        <p>Property lawyers and conveyancers often manage document collection for transactions. We work with conveyancers to translate the documentation packages they assemble, ensuring all documents are ready for registration together.</p>
        
        <h3>Developer Sales Teams</h3>
        <p>International sales teams at major developers regularly need translation support. We offer volume arrangements for developers with consistent translation needs, providing predictable pricing and dedicated contacts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Common Real Estate Translation Scenarios</h2>
      <div class="content-prose">
        <h3>Joint Ownership Registration</h3>
        <p>When married couples purchase property together, DLD may require marriage certificate translation. If the certificate is from abroad, it may also need attestation. We handle both translation and attestation coordination.</p>
        
        <h3>Company-Owned Property</h3>
        <p>Properties purchased through companies require corporate documentation: <a href="/legal/corporate/moa/">MOA translation</a>, board resolutions, shareholder information. We translate corporate documents with accuracy that satisfies both DLD and banking requirements.</p>
        
        <h3>Inheritance and Succession</h3>
        <p>Property passing through inheritance involves court procedures and documentation from multiple jurisdictions. Death certificates, probate documents, and heir identification documents may all need translation. We handle these sensitive documents with appropriate care.</p>
        
        <h3>Dispute Resolution</h3>
        <p>Property disputes before Dubai Courts or RERA require translated evidence. Contracts, correspondence, payment records—any document in a language other than Arabic needs certified translation for court submission. We provide <a href="/services/legal-translation/">legal translation</a> that meets court requirements.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <RelatedServices
        pageKey="realEstateIndustry"
        title="You May Also Need"
        showFamily={true}
        showCrossSilo={true}
        maxItems={6}
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container cta-section">
      <h2>Property Transaction Support</h2>
      <p>Whether you are a buyer, seller, agent, or developer, send us your property documents for a quick quote. We understand deal timelines and deliver accordingly.</p>
      <a href="https://wa.me/971508620217" class="btn btn-primary">
        <i class="fab fa-whatsapp"></i> Send Property Documents
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-section { padding: 8rem 0 4rem; background: var(--primary-color); }
  .breadcrumb { font-size: 0.85rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .breadcrumb a { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: none; }
  .breadcrumb a:hover { color: #ffffff; }
  .breadcrumb .separator { margin: 0 0.5rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); }
  .breadcrumb .current { color: #ffffff; }
  h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem); font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #ffffff; }
  .hero-subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--accent-color); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .hero-intro { font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8; max-width: 700px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); }
  
  .content-prose {
    max-width: 800px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  
  .content-prose h3 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }
  
  .content-prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-dark);
  }
  
  .content-prose a {
    color: var(--accent-color);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  
  .content-prose a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  
  .service-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; }
  .service-card { background: #ffffff; border-radius: 1rem; padding: 2rem; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); transition: all 0.3s ease; }
  .service-card:hover { transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); }
  .service-icon { width: 56px; height: 56px; border-radius: 14px; background: var(--primary-color); color: #ffffff; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .service-card h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.15rem; }
  .service-card p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .benefits-grid { display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .benefit-item { display: flex; gap: 1.25rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: #ffffff; border-radius: 0.75rem; }
  .benefit-item i { color: var(--accent-color); font-size: 1.5rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 0.25rem; }
  .benefit-item h4 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .benefit-item p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .cta-section { text-align: center; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .cta-section h2 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .cta-section p { margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 1rem 2rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.3s ease; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--accent-color); color: #ffffff; }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: #e0144c; transform: translateY(-2px); }
</style>
